<i>noun</i>: 수정 [수정], 수식 [수식], 변조 [변ː조] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>수정 [수정]</dt><br>
<dd>modification; amendment</dd><br>
<dd>잘못된 것을 바로잡거나 다듬어서 바르게 고침.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of correcting or refining a wrong thing so that it becomes right.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>수식 [수식]</dt><br>
<dd>1. decoration</dd><br>
<dd>겉모양을 꾸밈.</dd><br>
<dd>An adornment of the appearance.</dd><br>
<dd>2. embellishment</dd><br>
<dd>글이나 문장의 표현을 화려하고 기교 있게 꾸밈.</dd><br>
<dd>An embellishment of the expression in a composition or sentence in a fanciful and stylish manner.</dd><br>
<dd>3. modification</dd><br>
<dd>문법에서, 관형어나 부사어 등을 체언이나 용언에 덧붙여 그 뜻을 분명하게 하거나 꾸미는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A linguistic phenomenon in which an adnominal phrase, adverb, etc., relates to a substantive or a predicate in a sentence by way of specifying its meaning or qualifying it in other ways.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>변조 [변ː조]</dt><br>
<dd>1. change; modification</dd><br>
<dd>이미 만들어진 물건을 손질하여 다른 모양이나 다른 물건으로 바꾸어 만듦.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of mending an item that was already finished so that it is changed to another item or shape.</dd><br>
<dd>2. falsification</dd><br>
<dd>권한이 없는 사람이 문서, 화폐, 수표 등의 모양이나 내용을 다르게 바꿈.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of changing the shape or content of a document, check, money, etc., by a person with no authority.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>